I"°"<p>When you are writing <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language">HTML</abbr> (or any other programming language), well-written code follows consistent indentation and spacing patterns. In some languages, indentation and spacing are required for the code to function properly. In <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language">HTML</abbr>, inconsistent indentation and spacing will not impact the functionality of a website, but will cause your code to be difficult to read and understand.</p>

<h2 id="goal">Goal</h2>

<p>Follow along to learn:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Best practices for spacing <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language">HTML</abbr></li>
</ul>

